*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt *(handwritten)*

VASCULAR PLANTS OF GEORGIA

*Galax aphylla* L.

DIAPENSIACEAE

RABUN COUNTY. Clumped, infrequent
perennial on S-facing, shaded seepage slope,
organic acidic gravelly sand, bottom of Tallulah
Gorge, ca. 100 m N of the Georgia Power Co.
power station and ca. 40 m from Tallulah River.
Associated taxa: *Platanthera integrilabia*, *Parnassia
asarifolia*, *Osmunda regalis*, *Sphagnum* sp., *Carex* sp.
With Charles Edward Beard.

Collected: 10 June 1991 by Lawrence W. Zettler #817
Determined: 18 June 1991 by LWZ
